                <p class="fw-bold text-dark">Week 1: An in-depth examination of yoga poses</p>
                <p>Our curriculum aims to give students a comprehensive understanding of yoga, and the first week of instruction has proven this:</p>
                <ul class="disc__list">
	<li>Ashtanga Vinyasa: We present the <a href="https://rishikeshyognirvana.com/blog/ashtanga-primary-series.php#primary">initial series of Ashtanga Vinyasa</a>, emphasizing drishtis during asana practice, the foundations of <a href="https://rishikeshyognirvana.com/blog/mastering-the-sun-salutation.php">Sun Salutations A and B</a>, and the standing series.</li>
	<li>Vinyasa Flow: This <a href="https://rishikeshyognirvana.com/blog/vinyasa-yoga-guide.php">dynamic style of yoga</a> introduces students to the art of creating fluid sequences and incorporating stretches to enhance flexibility.</li>
	<li>Pranayama: Numerous techniques were used to explore breath control, a fundamental aspect of yoga, with a focus on the significance of diaphragmatic and yogic breathing, as well as <a class="link" href="&lt;?php echo $base_url;?&gt;blog/mastering-nadi-shodhana-pranayama.php">Nadi Shodhan</a> and Kapalbhati.</li>
	<li>Shatkarmas: The six purifying asanas of yoga, such as Jal Neti and Sutra Neti, are presented, emphasizing their function in mental and physical cleansing.</li>
	<li>Yoga Philosophy: We looked at the fundamentals of yoga, including its development and important lessons from Patanjali&#39;s Yoga Sutras, which emphasize the value of consistency and detachment.</li>
	<li>Alignment of the Body: Sun Salutations A and B postures are explained in detail, emphasizing the importance of exact alignment.</li>
	<li>Anatomy: The learning for the week includes a thorough examination of human anatomy, focusing on the skeletal system and how muscles work in different positions.</li>
	<li>Meditation: To enhance comprehension and practice, a variety of meditation methods, such as Trataka and humming meditation, are introduced.</li>
                </ul>

